Package: cld
Title: Create Compact Letter Display (CLD) for Statistical Comparisons
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Vilmantas",
           family = "Gegzna",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "GegznaV@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9500-5167"))
Description: Creates compact letter displays (CLDs) for visualizing results of 
    pairwise statistical comparisons from post-hoc tests. Groups sharing the 
    same letter are not significantly different from each other. Supports 
    multiple input formats including 'pairwise.htest' objects from base R 
    (e.g., pairwise.t.test(), pairwise.wilcox.test()), 'PMCMR' and 'PMCMRplus' 
    objects, 'posthoc_anova' objects from 'rstatix' (e.g., games_howell_test(), 
    tukey_hsd()), 'PostHocTest' and 'DunnTest' objects from 'DescTools', 
    symmetric matrices of p-values, and data frames with comparison results. 
    Provides a consistent, formula-based interface for generating statistical 
    grouping letters across different testing frameworks, commonly used in 
    agricultural, biological, and statistical reporting.
